This paper deals with building binary decision-making classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses fairness in decision-making, which is a growing area of research in computer science and can be categorized under cs.CY (Computational Social Science), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to post-processing classifiers, which involves deferring some decisions, and this can be seen as a form of active learning or online learning, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
